-- Egypt's pound stable on official and black markets
-- By Shadia Nasralla
-- Wed Jun 25, 2014 04:58AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, June 25 (Reuters) - The Egyptian pound was steady at a central bank dollar sale on Wednesday and on the black market.

The central bank said it sold $37.6 million at a cut-off price of 7.1401 pounds <CBEO>, leaving it unchanged from its last sale on Monday. It had offered $40 million. The dollar was offered for 7.40 pounds in the black market on Wednesday. The unofficial rates have been stable since last week.